excerpt: Upbeat island hangout with shopping, restaurants & a small amusement park with a Ferris wheel.
detail_description: Wolmido Island, located just off the coast of Incheon, South Korea, is a lively and popular destination known for its festive atmosphere and diverse attractions. Connected to the mainland by a bridge, this upbeat island offers visitors an array of experiences including shopping, dining at seafood restaurants, and enjoying a small amusement park with a Ferris wheel.
name: Wolmido

excerpt: Bustling tourist & cultural district known for its Chinese-owned restaurants & businesses.
detail_description: Chinatown Incheon is a bustling tourist and cultural district known for its Chinese-owned restaurants and businesses. Located in South Korea, it is the only official Chinatown in the country and has been around since 1884. The area boasts architectural flourishes, including three gateways or paifangs, with a giant memorial archway greeting visitors upon arrival.
name: Incheon Chinatown

excerpt: Park inspired by New York's Central Park featuring paths, meadows & a manmade lake with water taxis.
name: Songdo Central Park

excerpt: A zoo, botanical garden & large open areas are all located within this peaceful city park.
detail_description: Incheon Grand Park is a vast urban park nestled in the heart of Incheon, South Korea, providing a tranquil escape from the city's hustle and bustle. Spanning 727 acres, it features a zoo, botanical garden, open green spaces, and various recreational activities. The children's zoo houses over 200 animals including Japanese macaques and ostriches.
name: Incheon Grand Park

excerpt: Many of the houses in this village are decorated in bright colours with depictions of fairy tales.
detail_description: Songwol-dong Fairy Tale Village is a vibrant and whimsical attraction located near Incheon Chinatown. Once a settlement for foreigners, the village was revitalized with colorful murals and sculptures depicting classic fairy tales. The houses are adorned with bright colors and images of famous cartoon characters, creating a dreamy atmosphere that attracts many young visitors. It's a perfect spot for taking photos and immersing oneself in the enchanting world of fairy tales.
name: Songwol-dong Fairy Tale Village
address: Jayugongwonseo-ro 45beon-gil, Songwol-dong 3(sam)-ga, Jung-gu, Incheon, South Korea

excerpt: Busy, open-air marketplace featuring stalls with prepared foods, clothing, produce, meats & gifts.
detail_description: Sinpo International Market in Incheon is a bustling open-air marketplace that has been around since the late 19th century. It was officially established in 1970 and has become a representative market of Incheon, especially popular among tourists arriving by ferry and cruise boats. The market offers a wide variety of goods, including prepared foods, clothing, produce, meats, and gifts.
name: Sinpo International Market, Incheon

excerpt: Ultra-modern skyscraper home to offices, eateries & an observation floor with city panoramas.
detail_description: G-Tower is a cutting-edge skyscraper located in Songdo International City, offering a mix of offices, dining options, and an observation floor providing stunning city vistas. This architectural marvel by Zaha Hadid stands at 150 meters and houses international organizations like the United Nations. Visitors can explore the outdoor observatory at the pinnacle and enjoy the lush Sky Garden on the 29th floor with its indoor greenery and panoramic views over Central Park and Incheon Bridge.
name: G-Tower
address: 175 Art center-daero, Yeonsu-gu, Incheon, South Korea

detail_description: Nestled in the hilly Songhyun Park in Dong-gu, the Sudoguksan Museum of Housing & Living offers a captivating glimpse into Incheon's past. The museum delves into the history of the daldongne, or 'moon villages,' which were temporary settlements for the impoverished that emerged on Incheon's hilltops during the 1960s and 70s.
name: Sudoguksan Museum of Housing & Living, Incheon

excerpt: Hilltop memorial & exhibition hall with photos & models commemorating a crucial Korean War battle.
detail_description: Nestled atop a hill in Incheon, the Memorial Hall for Incheon Landing Operation stands as a poignant reminder of the bravery displayed during one of the Korean War's most significant battles. Opened in 1984 to mark the centenary of Incheon Port's opening to international trade, this hall is dedicated to honoring the soldiers who fought valiantly under General MacArthur’s command in 1950.
name: Memorial Hall for Incheon Landing Operation

excerpt: Incheon, a South Korean city bordering the capital of Seoul, has long been a transportation hub. The ultramodern, massive Incheon International Airport, with railway connections to Seoul, features a casino, spa and golf course. Yeonan Pier, close to the popular Incheon Fish Market, is the starting point for many boat tours. Incheon is also known for its beach-lined islands, including Yeongjong and Muui-dong.
detail_description: Incheon, a bustling South Korean city adjacent to Seoul, is renowned for its modern infrastructure and rich cultural heritage. The city is home to the impressive Incheon International Airport, offering various amenities such as a casino, spa, and golf course. Additionally, Yeonan Pier serves as a gateway to boat tours and is situated near the popular Incheon Fish Market. Incheon's picturesque islands like Yeongjong and Muui-dong are famous for their beautiful beaches.
name: Incheon

excerpt: Local landmark hosting a regular lineup of varied exhibitions, conferences & performances.
detail_description: Tri-bowl is a cultural complex located in Songdo, featuring an architectural gem consisting of three hemispheres sitting on water. It hosts various exhibitions, conferences, and performances, making it a local landmark. Visitors can stroll along the paved paths underneath the structure and enjoy the beautiful illumination of Tri-Bowl at night, reflecting on the water's surface. While some find it smaller than expected from pictures, others appreciate its imposing architecture and its resonance with sound during events.
name: Tri-bowl

excerpt: Tranquil park featuring salt marshes, migratory birds, observation areas & a nature center.
detail_description: Sorae Ecology Park is a serene and tranquil destination featuring salt marshes, migratory birds, observation areas, and a nature center. Once a salt production site, it has transformed into a haven for migratory birds since 2009. The park offers opportunities for biking and photography amidst lush greenery. It's also known as a filming location for the popular 'A Korean Odyssey' series.
name: Sorae Ecology Park

excerpt: Popular destination offering rides & an indoor playground for kids, including water activities.
detail_description: Wolmi Theme Park, located in the Wolmido Culture Street area of Incheon, South Korea, is a popular destination for families and tourists. The park offers a variety of rides and an indoor playground with water activities for kids. Visitors can also enjoy attractions such as the Wolmido Moonlight Music Fountain, Observatory, Cloud Hill, and Waterfront Tech in the surrounding area.
name: Wolmi Theme Park

detail_description: Incheon Art Platform is a must-see for art enthusiasts visiting South Korea. Situated in the lively city of Incheon, this unique destination offers an immersive experience in the local art scene. Housed in a renovated elementary school building, it exudes charm and character. The platform serves as a cultural hub showcasing contemporary art that challenges and inspires visitors. It's also a creative oasis for artists, providing co-working studio spaces and galleries to work and exhibit their pieces.
name: Incheon Art Platform

detail_description: The Incheon City Museum, located near the Memorial Hall for Incheon Landing Operation, offers a comprehensive look at the history and culture of Incheon. Situated in Yeonsu-gu, it was initially built around the ridge at Jayu Park and currently houses around 4300 artifacts. The museum features three exhibition halls showcasing Incheon's rich history, an outdoor museum, and exhibits on topics such as the evolution of phones.
name: Incheon City Museum

excerpt: Sprawling spa facility offering themed sauna rooms, jacuzzis, a pool, eatery & movie theater.
detail_description: Spasis is a sprawling spa facility in Incheon, offering various amenities such as themed sauna rooms, jacuzzis, a pool, an eatery, and even a movie theater. It's known for its traditional bathhouses called Jjimjilbang where visitors can unwind after exploring Korean art and culture. The entrance fee is 9000 won with additional services like body scrubs available at an extra cost.
name: Spasis
address: 263 Gyeongin-ro, Dohwa-dong, Michuhol-gu, Incheon, South Korea

excerpt: Paved trails wind through this hilly park known for spring cherry blossoms & dramatic fall foliage.
detail_description: Freedom Park, also known as Incheon Jayu Park, is a significant landmark in Incheon, South Korea, dedicated to honoring historical sacrifices and victories while celebrating freedom and democracy. The park features paved trails perfect for strolling amidst spring cherry blossoms and vibrant fall foliage. Visitors can explore memorials, monuments, and cultural attractions that offer a meaningful journey through history.
name: Jayu Park (Freedom Park)

excerpt: Large, sophisticated hub of upscale stores offering clothing & accessories at below-retail prices.
detail_description: The Hyundai Premium Outlet in Songdo is a high-end shopping destination featuring a vast array of upscale stores that offer clothing, accessories and other luxury items at discounted prices. The outdoor mall is well-designed and spacious, with plenty of options for dining and entertainment. Additionally, there are several restaurants nearby for those looking to enjoy a meal before or after their shopping experience.
name: Hyundai Premium Outlets Songdo

detail_description: Wolmi Park, situated in Incheon, South Korea, is a popular attraction that seamlessly combines history, culture, and natural beauty. The park features traditional Korean structures such as pavilions and marketplaces. Visitors can explore various trails offering scenic views of Incheon from the observatory. Additionally, there's a Hanok village where one can dress in hanbok for memorable photos. The well-maintained gardens and clean facilities make it an enjoyable experience for all visitors.
name: 월미공원

detail_description: Incheon Complex Fish Market is a bustling hub for seafood enthusiasts, offering the freshest catch and an authentic glimpse into local life. Visitors can purchase seafood and have it expertly prepared at nearby restaurants. Arriving early in the morning allows for a firsthand view of lively fish auctions. While transportation to the market may require some navigation, the experience of indulging in fresh seafood dishes makes it well worth the effort.
name: Incheon Complex Fish Market

detail_description: Gyeongin Ara Waterway Passenger Terminal is a picturesque route that links the Hangang River to the Yellow Sea, offering an array of attractions such as an observatory, artificial waterfall, and Sculpture Park. Visitors can leisurely stroll along the promenade or opt for a bike ride on the 18.2-kilometer bicycle path that runs alongside the waterway. The terminal also features a beautiful passenger ship set against a park backdrop, providing a serene environment for relaxation and enjoyment.
name: Gyeongin Ara Waterway Passenger Terminal
An's Bakery
address: South Korea, Incheon, 연수고 Central-ro, 160, KR 인천광역시 연수구

detail_description: Incheon National University (INU), Songdo Campus is a highly regarded educational institution, particularly for students pursuing Engineering. The campus boasts stunning surroundings and offers the opportunity to enjoy leisurely walks along the seaside in the evenings. INU is known as a leading startup university in Incheon, providing excellent opportunities for aspiring entrepreneurs. It offers a wide range of studies across various fields of expertise. Those who have visited or studied at INU often express their admiration and love for this outstanding institution.
name: Incheon National University (INU), Songdo Campus

detail_description: The National Institute of Biological Resources is a leading preservation facility in Asia, showcasing around 6,000 species collected from roadkills or natural deaths. It features unique species like the Korean rose bitterling and provides an educational experience for visitors. The institute offers free parking and admission, making it a great place to visit with children. Additionally, there are plans for new exhibition rooms and outdoor spaces for leisure activities. This destination is highly recommended for families and individuals interested in Korea's diverse flora and fauna.
name: National Institute of Biological Resources

excerpt: Fish market packed with tanks of live catch & known for seasonal blue crab, with on-site eateries.
name: Soraepogu Traditional Fish Market

detail_description: Songdo Hanok Village is a modern interpretation of a traditional hanok village, offering visitors the opportunity to experience the charm of a hanok village in Incheon. It's an ideal spot for capturing beautiful photos and immersing yourself in Korean culture. The village features hanok-style cafes, restaurants, and even a hotel. Whether you're strolling through during the day or at night, the picturesque surroundings make for an aesthetically pleasing visit.
name: Songdo Hanok Village

excerpt: Children's museum offering a variety of hands-on activities, including a dinosaur exploration room.
detail_description: Incheon Children's Museum, located near Munhak Stadium, is a popular destination for families with young children. The museum offers various hands-on activities and art exhibitions tailored to kids. One of its highlights is the dinosaur exploration room featuring a gallery of giant dinosaur statues that kids will love. While some visitors find the facilities a bit old, others are pleasantly surprised by the interesting and educational exhibits suitable for both children and adults.
name: Incheon Children's Museum

detail_description: Sunrise (Haedoji) Park in Songdo is a diverse and beautiful park that offers something for everyone. It hosts a stunning rose festival in May and provides an ideal spot for picnics on weekends. The park features multiple children's playgrounds, including large slides and a sandbox, as well as hammocks for seasonal napping.
name: 해돋이공원

detail_description: East Boat House, situated at the eastern end of Songdo Central Park, offers a variety of water leisure activities with stunning views of green parks and skyscrapers along the waterfront. Visitors can rent boats to explore the river and enjoy the picturesque scenery. The F-Boat rentals provide a unique experience with clear plastic covers to protect from harsh weather conditions. Additionally, visitors can relax at the coffee shop on the second floor while waiting for their companions.
name: East Boat House

detail_description: Bupyeong Culture Street, located in Incheon, is a lively and colorful hub known for its street art, indie music scene, and trendy cafes. The area is adorned with vibrant murals and graffiti, while quirky shops offer handmade crafts and souvenirs. Visitors can immerse themselves in live music performances, savor street food delights, and soak up the bustling atmosphere. The location boasts great accessibility via public transportation from Bupyeong Station Shopping Mall Underground Shopping Mall No.
name: Bupyeong Culture Street
address: 78-2 Bupyeongmunhwa-ro, Bupyeong District, Incheon, South Korea

detail_description: Cheongna Lake Park, located in Cheongna International City, Incheon, South Korea, is a serene and picturesque retreat offering diverse recreational activities. The park features scenic landscapes and a tranquil lake that provides a perfect setting for unwinding and connecting with nature. Visitors can enjoy wheelchair biking, clean air, and various rest areas throughout the park. Additionally, there are opportunities to witness a fountain show and feed fish and ducks.
name: 청라 호수공원 (청라 센트럴레이크파크)

detail_description: The Bupyeong Underground Shopping Center is a vast underground marketplace with over 1,400 stalls offering a wide variety of products. While the quality may not be top-notch, it's a convenient place to find clothing, bags, souvenirs, phone accessories, party supplies, and more. The top floor features a food court with various privately-owned restaurants offering affordable and delicious meals. This shopping center is particularly suitable for finding items for kids and spouses at budget-friendly prices.
name: Underground Shopping
address: 69 Bupyeong-daero, 부평1동, Bupyeong District, Incheon, South Korea

detail_description: NC Cube Canal Walk is a unique shopping and leisure destination known as the 'another Garosu-gil.' It boasts an artificial canal flowing through block-shaped buildings, creating a European-style street with 340 shops. Each block specializes in shopping, culture, food, and relaxation. The architectural aesthetics and cultural elements contribute to a lively and exotic atmosphere. While the distance from the station may be inconvenient, visitors can enjoy good restaurants and experience a bustling commercial district.
name: Canal Walk

detail_description: Ara Canal Sicheon Garam Place is an 18-kilometer waterway that connects the Han River to the Yellow Sea, running from Incheon's Seo-gu district to Seoul's Gangseo-gu. As Korea's first inland waterway, it offers a unique experience with impressive features such as the artificial Ara Waterfall and the inspiring AraMaru Skywalk Bridge. Visitors can take a break at small parks along the canal and enjoy some fresh air in the evening.
name: Ara Canal Sicheon Garam Place

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Incheon's Guwol-dong, Moraenae Market has a rich history dating back to its establishment in May 1982. Initially a wholesale market for agricultural and fisheries products, it has since evolved to offer an array of goods including clothing, tableware, and more. Renowned for its bustling atmosphere and diverse offerings, the market prides itself on staying current with fresh and trendy items.
name: Moraenae Market

detail_description: Incheon's Chinatown is the sole officially recognized Chinatown in South Korea, with a history dating back to 1884. The area features traditional Chinese-style architecture, including a main gate, steps, and sculptures. Visitors can explore Chinese restaurants and immerse themselves in the bustling yet captivating atmosphere. It's an ideal place for leisurely strolls while soaking up the rich cultural ambiance and surroundings.
name: Incheon China Town

detail_description: The National Museum of World Writing Systems is a unique institution dedicated to the history and evolution of writing systems from around 2100 BCE to the present day. The museum features artifacts, information, and insights into various writing mediums, their historical significance, and contemporary usage. Visitors can explore ancient scripts from China and India, as well as innovative exhibits like the Tower of Babel. The museum also offers hands-on learning programs for children, with interactive activities such as puzzle games and tablet games.
name: National Museum of World Writing Systems

detail_description: Geogung is a well-known Korean restaurant with multiple locations, including one at 157 2Honestar 2F, Songdo Gukjae-daero, Yeonsu-gu, Incheon. The restaurant's operating hours are from 11:00 to 22:00. One of their standout dishes is the 'Incheon Rice,' which has gained popularity among locals for its unique flavors and presentation.
name: Geogung
address: 28 Gwangjang-ro, Bupyeong District, Incheon, South Korea

detail_description: Gomang-Go, also known as Freedom Park or Jayu Park, is Incheon's first western-style park. It was named in 1957 to commemorate Korea's freedom from the war. The park not only holds historical significance but also offers picturesque spots. Visitors can enjoy delicious mango juice at a nearby cafe and appreciate the friendly service from the staff.
name: Gomang-Go
address: 138-5 번지 1층 Juan-dong, Michuhol-gu, Incheon, South Korea

detail_description: Sunrise Park, nestled behind the Oakwood Premier Incheon, is a jogging enthusiast's paradise. This beautifully designed park pays homage to Incheon's rich history as a port and its journey towards modernization. With impressive wind power generators adorning the landscape and Songdo Hill offering panoramic views of the area, it's an ideal spot for both exercise and relaxation. Families will find joy in its vibrant azaleas and roses blooming across expansive lawns where children can play freely.
name: Sunrise Park

excerpt: Multi-sectioned bridge linking Yeongjong Island with the mainland & built to withstand earthquakes.
detail_description: The Incheon Bridge is a multi-sectioned cable-stayed bridge that connects Yeongjong Island with mainland South Korea. It was designed to withstand earthquakes and is the world's tenth longest cable-stayed bridge, spanning 21.38 kms. This engineering marvel links the Incheon International Airport with the rest of South Korea and has become a popular landmark in Incheon due to its stunning light works at night.
name: Incheon Bridge

excerpt: Colorfully painted, serene Buddhist temple compound with ornate carvings & many old-growth trees.
detail_description: Jeondeungsa Temple is a serene and colorful Buddhist temple compound nestled among old-growth trees. The temple features ornate carvings and has a unique history, making it a must-visit for history lovers and those interested in Korean culture. While some parts of the temple are under renovation, visitors can still explore the beautiful grounds and various buildings. It's recommended to wear hiking shoes due to the steep hike, and there are souvenir shops both inside and outside the temple.
name: Jeondeungsa Temple
address: 37-41 Jeondeungsa-ro, Gilsang-myeon, Ganghwa-gun, Incheon, South Korea

excerpt: Complex on the North Korean border featuring information about the country & an observation deck.
detail_description: The Ganghwa Peace Observatory is a complex located on the North Korean border that offers a unique opportunity to observe daily life in North Korea through binoculars for a fee of 500 won. The area is heavily guarded by active military sentries and has a checkpoint on the way. A historical and informative observation building with displays in Korean and English can be found, along with a small shop and restaurants inside.
name: Ganghwa Peace Observatory
address: 797 Jeonmangdae-ro, Yangsa-myeon, Ganghwa-gun, Incheon, South Korea

detail_description: Gyeyangsan, a magnificent mountain peak in Incheon, impresses with its well-maintained trails and friendly atmosphere. It offers easy hiking paths suitable for all ages and boasts convenient transportation options. As the second highest mountain in the area, it provides breathtaking views of Incheon from its rocky trails and beautiful rose garden. It's a popular spot for picnics, where visitors can enjoy the stunning scenery while indulging in food.
name: Gyeyangsan

excerpt: 50,000-capacity stadium complex with its own subway station & separate soccer & baseball fields.
detail_description: Incheon Munhak Stadium is a massive sports complex located in Michuhol-gu, Incheon. It features a 50,000-capacity main stadium, an auxiliary stadium, and a baseball field. The complex also includes a sports center and various amenities. As the home ground of Incheon United FC, it's a must-visit for football fans to experience the vibrant sports culture of the city.
name: Incheon Munhak Stadium
